50|$|Bruins' player George Owen was {{the first}} NHL player to {{regularly}} <b>wear</b> <b>headgear</b> for protective purposes. Prior to this, the only time protective <b>headgear</b> was <b>worn</b> was to temporarily protect injuries. Fifty-one years later the NHL would mandate the use of helmets. Craig MacTavish was the last NHL player to not wear a helmet, retiring in 1997.|$|R
