50|$|At the University of Cambridge, {{undergraduates}} {{by ancient}} convention used {{to cut their}} tassels very short so that the tassel does not extend beyond {{the edge of the}} board. After they graduated, they wore the square cap with the tassel at the normal length. This convention has now fallen into disuse; few people now <b>wear</b> <b>headgear</b> with academic dress at any time and undergraduates in particular have no need to wear the cap.|$|R
50|$|House {{rules are}} rules {{applying}} {{only in a}} certain location or organization. Bars and pubs in which games take place frequently have house rules posted. For example, it is a house rule in United States Air Force officers' clubs that if an officer enters the club <b>wearing</b> <b>headgear</b> and is officially noticed (i.e., the bell near the bar is rung), the entering officer must buy a round of drinks for the bar.|$|R
